texts.text: >The next day, the Liberators meet at Kouki's temple.
>They plan to discuss counter-measures against Indrajit, but...
Jeez, how long have we been here?
About an hour.
About two hours.
I wouldn't go that far. I'd say one hour at best.
Isn't he kinda late?
Not at all. This is peanuts.
You've never waited for Shionyan to exit after a concert.
It can take up to 8 hours, depending on her mood.
That sounds a lot like criticism.
Stay kneeled until Indra gets here. Do it.
Yes, ma'am!
Man, groupies have it rough...
Ain't punctuality the Japanese way? That god comin' or what?
He should be here soon.
In the meantime, shall we break a sweat together, Vince?
I'm good. Call me when Indra decides to show up.
I'll take that as a polite pass.
What about you, Kouki? Ready for an impromptu workout?
Oh, right. For tomorrow.
(What troubles you, Lord Indra?)
>Two hours later...
Jeez, how long have we been here?
About three hours.
About five hours.
It's been about three hours, but I agree it feels much longer.
Seriously! He's taking forever!
Hey, Mister Meat.
Sorry, can't talk now.
Ugh, you look constipated.
He's been kneeling for two hours.
Koden, why not forgive him already?
You heard him, so how about it?
Continue or keep going?
The former, obviously.
And there you have it.
Wait, both mean the same thing though...
*Sigh* He's takin' his sweet time.
Any idea what's goin' on, Kouki?
I'm as lost as you are.
(Lord Indra...)
>Indra never shows up that day.
Sorry, Kouki. We overstayed our welcome before your big match.
I'll be fine. But what about the rest of you?
Yeah, well, looks like Indra isn't showing up.
Hey, can I ask you something that's been on my mind?
This is a surprise, but sure.
Our enemy this time is "Indrajit,"
and the god we asked for help is "Indra."
Why're their names so similar? Is there a reason?
Right, we haven't yet discussed the connection between them.
No time like the present. Let's all get on the same page.
He wasn't always "Indrajit."
His true name is "Meganada."
"Indrajit" is a title of sorts.
It means "Conqueror of Indra."
"Conqueror"? Then...
Yeah. In the epic poems of old,
Indra fell to Indrajit.
This was due to some historical events of the period.
Indra was once worshipped as a god and beloved by many.
However, people's beliefs shifted and evolved over time.
Fewer followers inevitably diminishes a demon's strength.
He lost to Meganada soon after,
and that's how Indrajit got his annoying moniker.
So, it's a rematch with an old nemesis. ...Sounds complicated.
I never knew...
Really? I figured you were an Indra expert compared to us.
After all, doesn't your temple worship him?
Haha. Guess I need to read up on Hinduism.
Ah, but I've practically memorized the Rig Veda already.
My grandma often told me of Lord Indra's great exploits.
I was captivated by those tales of his unrivaled strength.
Now that I think about it,
I probably became a boxer because I wanted to be like Lord Indra.
To you, Indra is a benchmark.
Yeah, definitely.
He's the mightiest of gods.
*Snort* "The mightiest?" That guy? You're a comedian.
...Say that again. I dare you.
Knock it off, Vince.
He kept us waitin' all day. I've got a right to complain.
At any rate, I wouldn't expect too much from Indra.
What?
Gods like him fade with the past.
He's dealin' with the symbol of his own decline.
Who can blame him for runnin' away like a coward?
Bastard!
Kouki, please stop!
>Jeng Yun fights to hold back the enraged Kouki.
I know Lord Indra isn't like that!
He'd never run away!!
Hah! Whatever you say, kid.
Vince, that's enough.
Sorry, Kouki. It's just his personality.
Still, it's true Indra is MIA.
We should assume we're on our own and move forward.
Things will only get worse the longer we wait.
Let's pick this back up at the Hideout.
Apologies, Kouki. I know tomorrow is the big tournament.
Please do your best. I'll be rooting for you.
>The next day.
It's raining out.
This sucks. Today's match is critical.
...Lord Indra never did come back.
Maybe he really...
No! I can't think like that! Not today!
Lord Indra! You're the reason I've walked this path!
However, that ends today.
I'll go out with a bang!
Are you sure about this, Kouki?
Even if you run from your decline, you'll find no salvation.
No matter how many times you fall, you must get back up.
Both you and I.
